<img class="alignnone wp-image-1222" src="http://wellnessway4u.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/images-97.jpeg" alt="Big Toe Pose (iStock)" width="366" height="244" />
<h3>Steps to Perform Big Toe Pose Yoga (Padangusthasana)</h3>
<strong>Start in Tadasana (Mountain Pose):</strong>
Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart. Distribute your weight evenly across both feet and engage your core.

<img class="alignnone wp-image-1223" src="http://wellnessway4u.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/images-98.jpeg" alt="Tadasana (Yogateket)" width="395" height="259" />

<strong>Prepare to Bend Forward:</strong>
Take a deep breath in, and as you exhale, hinge forward at your hips. Keep your spine long and avoid rounding your back.

<img class="alignnone wp-image-1224" src="http://wellnessway4u.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/images-99.jpeg" alt="Bend Forward (Ekhart Yoga)" width="285" height="285" />

<strong>Grab Your Toes:</strong>
Use your index and middle fingers to hook around your big toes. Bend your knees slightly if needed to avoid strain.

<img class="alignnone wp-image-1225" src="http://wellnessway4u.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/images-100.jpeg" alt="Grab Your Toes ( Medium ) " width="323" height="242" />

<strong>Lengthen and Fold:</strong>
Inhale to lengthen your spine, then exhale to fold deeper, bending your elbows outward for a deeper stretch.

<img class="alignnone wp-image-1226" src="http://wellnessway4u.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/images-2024-11-20T131411.269.jpeg" alt="Lengthen and Fold ( Temple Yatri)" width="378" height="212" />

<strong>Hold and Release:</strong>
Hold the pose for 5-10 breaths, then release your toes and slowly rise back up to standing on an inhale.

<img class="alignnone wp-image-1227" src="http://wellnessway4u.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/images-2024-11-20T132236.660.jpeg" alt="Hold and Release ( Freepik)" width="270" height="481" />
